This is solution to the problem that vlc cannnot be run as root
sudo sed -i 's/geteuid/getppid/' /usr/bin/vlc

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

THis is command to start php server through terminal.
GO to folder using "cd opt/lampp/"
sudo ./manager-linux-x64.run

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

THis is command to know current swapiness of the system
cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness

Command to change swapiness of the system
sudo sysctl vm.swappiness=1

After this open a file by this command
sudo gedit /etc/sysctl.conf

Paste this in this file
vm.swappiness = 1

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To give access of read and write to a file or folder.
sudo chmod a+rwx /path/to/file
if wanna give access to all folder and files of that folder omit x in given command.

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

To install lightdm
sudo apt-get install lightdm
To reconfigure lightdm
sudo dpkg-reconfigure lightdm

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

TO Configure postfix
sudo dpkg-reconfigure postfix
sudo service postfix restart

Then access this file and change parameters
sudo nano /etc/postfix/main.cf

Use this to test.
echo "This email confirms that Postfix is working" | mail -s "Testing Posfix" avaneeshdyadav@gmail.com
